HEADWORD: Muggy
<hw>Mug"gy</hw> <pr>(m⟦ucr⟧g"g⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Muggier</adjf>
<pr>(m⟦ucr⟧g"g⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Muggiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[Cf. Icel. <ets>mugga</ets> mist,
mugginess. Cf. 4th <er>Mold</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Moist; damp;
moldy; <as>as, <ex>muggy</ex> straw</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Warm, damp, and windless; uncomfortably hot and
humid; sultry; <as>as, <ex>muggy</ex> air, weather</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 952 --></p>

